<%- include('../partials/header') %>
    
<main class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row mb-4">
        <div class="col">
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-primary"><%= title %></h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted">A professional guide to exploring the rugged trails, ancient history, and dramatic high altitudes of the Peruvian Andes.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row align-items-center mb-5">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            
            <p>Hiking in the Cusco region is unlike trekking anywhere else on earth. Situated at an elevation of 3,399 meters (11,150 feet), the city of Cusco serves as the gateway to pristine alpine circuits and ancient stone trails. Managing the thin air is the most critical logistical step for any expedition.</p>
            <p>As a professional trekking guide, my first rule for travelers is authentic physical preparation: taking the proactive time to acclimatize for at least 48 to 72 hours before attempting heavy elevation gains. This foundational patience unlocks a safe, breathtaking connection with the landscape architecture of the Andes.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
            <img src="/images/cusco-trail.webp" alt="Scenic mountain trail in Cusco Peru" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm">
            <div class="mt-2 text-muted small italic">
                <p>Source: Personal guiding archive of Lourdes Soto.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>